import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['delay'])
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['delay', 'distance'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay')
    ax.set_title('How does distance relate to delay?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='box')
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Mean delay time: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean())])
    plt.title('What is the average delay time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='time')
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['delay'])
    plt.title('How does delay vary over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
